Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: No contact with victim.

10:18 AM Defendant Kasey T. Warwick in court, in custody.  Kelly L Hays appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Kasey T. Warwick appeared by video means. All parties via zoom.   Def. has copy of complaint, advised of charges and penalties.  Def. given atty rights and given 3 options, PD, hire own or court appointed atty.  Def. did reach out to P.D. and is eligible. Def. is on a probation hold.  State gives bail bond recommendation and bond recommendation. Court orders $5,000 cash bond with no contact with victim. Court will reserve right to be heard on bond @ later date. Def. makes statement RE: social worker.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for February 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
